<div class="entry-content"><div class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden" style="display: none;"><img width="900" height="1600" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-with-Garlic-Parmesan-Cream-Sauce-PIN.jpg"  data-pin-title="Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce (Easy Surf and Turf Recipe!)" data-pin-description="This Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce is restaurant-quality surf and turf made easy! Juicy ribeye steak and perfectly seared shrimp in the most luscious creamy garlic parmesan sauce with fresh spinach and lemon. Everything cooks in one skillet for easy cleanup. Perfect for date night, Valentine&#039;s Day, anniversaries, or any special occasion. With 75+ five-star reviews, this is one of our most popular recipes! You can use store-bought ingredients and have dinner on the table in under an hour."  alt="Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce." class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-inner"  /></div><div class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden" style="display: none;"><img width="900" height="1600" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-with-Garlic-Parmesan-Cream-Sauce-PIN.jpg"  data-pin-title="Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce (Easy Surf and Turf Recipe!)" data-pin-description="This Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce is restaurant-quality surf and turf made easy! Juicy ribeye steak and perfectly seared shrimp in the most luscious creamy garlic parmesan sauce with fresh spinach and lemon. Everything cooks in one skillet for easy cleanup. Perfect for date night, Valentine&#039;s Day, anniversaries, or any special occasion. With 75+ five-star reviews, this is one of our most popular recipes! You can use store-bought ingredients and have dinner on the table in under an hour."  alt="Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce." class="dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-inner  dpsp-post-pinterest-image-hidden-single"  /></div><span id="dpsp-post-content-markup" data-image-pin-it="true"></span>
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p class="has-text-align-left has-theme-button-color has-text-color">This <strong>Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce</strong> tastes like something you'd order at a steakhouse - but it comes together in one skillet in under an hour! Juicy ribeye, perfectly seared shrimp, and the most luscious creamy garlic parmesan sauce with fresh spinach and a squeeze of lemon. It looks fancy, it tastes incredible, and it's shockingly easy to pull off. No wonder it's one of our most popular recipes! &#129316;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1799" fetchpriority="high" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-19.jpg" alt="close up and delicious shot of a steak and seafood skillet with garlic parmesan cream sauce, fresh parsley, and parmesan flakes." data-skip-lazy class="wp-image-42163" style="object-fit:cover" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-19.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-19-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-19-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-19-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-19.jpg"></figure>    <div class="dpsp-email-save-this-tool " style="background-color: #f4e4e1;">        <div class="hubbub-save-this-form-wrapper"><h3 class="hubbub-save-this-heading">Save This Recipe! &#128140;</h3><div class="hubbub-save-this-message"><p>We'll email this post to you, so you can come back to it later!</p></div><div class="hubbub-save-this-form-only-wrapper"><form name="hubbub-save-this-form" method="post" action="">                    <input type="text" name="hubbub-save-this-snare" class="hubbub-save-this-snare hubbub-block-save-this-snare"><p class="hubbub-save-this-name-paragraph-wrapper"><input aria-label="First Name" type="text" placeholder="First Name" name="hubbub-save-this-name" value="" class="hubbub-block-save-this-text-control hubbub-save-this-name" required></p><p class="hubbub-save-this-emailaddress-paragraph-wrapper"><input aria-label="Email Address" type="email" placeholder="Email Address" name="hubbub-save-this-emailaddress" value="" class="hubbub-block-save-this-text-control hubbub-save-this-emailaddress" required></p><p class="hubbub-save-this-consent-paragraph-wrapper"><input type="checkbox" name="hubbub-save-this-consent" class="hubbub-save-this-consent" value="1" required> <label for="hubbub-save-this-consent">I agree to be sent email.</label></p><p class="hubbub-save-this-submit-button-paragraph-wrapper"><input type="submit" style="background-color:#2d4654;color:#ffffff;" value="Save This Recipe" class="hubbub-block-save-this-submit-button" name="hubbub-block-save-this-submit-button"></p><input type="hidden" name="hubbub-save-this-postid" class="hubbub-save-this-postid" value="25950">                    <input type="hidden" name="hubbub-save-this-posturl" class="hubbub-save-this-posturl" value="https://afullliving.com/steak-and-seafood-garlic-parmesan-cream-sauce/">                    <input type="hidden" name="hubbub-save-this-posttitle" class="hubbub-save-this-posttitle" value="Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce"></form>            </div></div>    </div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-this-garlic-parmesan-steak-and-shrimp-has-75-five-star-reviews-for-a-reason">This Garlic Parmesan Steak and Shrimp Has 75+ Five-Star Reviews for a Reason &#11088;</h2>



<p>We've been making this recipe for <em>years</em>, and our readers can't get enough of it. It shows up at anniversary dinners, Valentine's Day tables, holiday meals - basically any time someone wants to impress. The comments are full of people saying they got rave reviews at dinner parties, that their families asked for seconds, and that this is now their go-to special occasion recipe. (We're seriously<em> so</em> honored! &#129401;)</p>



<p>The secret is that creamy garlic parmesan sauce. It's rich, luscious, and coats every bite of perfectly seared steak and tender shrimp. Add fresh spinach, a squeeze of lemon, and you've got restaurant-quality surf and turf in one skillet. Everything cooks in the same pan, so cleanup is actually manageable even when you're cooking something this good.</p>



<p>Whether you're planning a special date night or just want to treat yourself on a random Tuesday, this is the recipe. Let's get into it!</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredients-for-this-surf-and-turf-skillet">Ingredients for this Surf and Turf Skillet &#129424;&#129385;</h2>



<p>This recipe keeps it simple with ingredients you probably already have on hand, or can easily grab at the grocery store. Fresh parmesan (not pre-shredded!) is the only non-negotiable for that silky, creamy sauce.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1799" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201799'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="ingredients to make a steak and seafood recipe, with steak, shrimp, parmesan cheese, stock, heavy cream, spinach, salt and pepper, red pepper flakes, smoked paprika, lemon, butter, olive oil, parsley, onion, and garlic with text to denote. " class="wp-image-42179" style="object-fit:cover" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic.png 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic-768x1151.png 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic-1025x1536.png 1025w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic-150x225.png 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic.png" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic.png"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1799" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic.png" alt="ingredients to make a steak and seafood recipe, with steak, shrimp, parmesan cheese, stock, heavy cream, spinach, salt and pepper, red pepper flakes, smoked paprika, lemon, butter, olive oil, parsley, onion, and garlic with text to denote. " class="wp-image-42179" style="object-fit:cover" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic.png 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic-768x1151.png 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic-1025x1536.png 1025w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic-150x225.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-Ingredients-Graphic.png"></noscript></figure></div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-creamy-garlic-parmesan-shrimp-and-steak">How to Make Creamy Garlic Parmesan Shrimp and Steak &#10024;</h2>



<p>Don't let the restaurant vibes intimidate you - this comes together in just a few simple steps, all in one skillet!</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-1 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="ribeye steak on a plate seasoned with salt and pepper." class="wp-image-42168" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3.jpg" alt="ribeye steak on a plate seasoned with salt and pepper." class="wp-image-42168" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-3.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ol start="1" class="wp-block-list is-style-circle-number-list">
<li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Season your <strong>steaks</strong> generously with <strong>kosher salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> on both sides. We're talking a really good coating here - don't be shy! The salt creates that beautiful crust when it hits the hot skillet.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-branding-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#129385; <strong>What steak should you use?</strong> We love ribeye for this because it's so flavorful and tender, but any good steak works! Sirloin, strip steak, filet mignon, or even <a href="https://afullliving.com/bavette-steak-recipe/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer">bavette steak</a> would be delicious. Just pick a cut you enjoy and cook it to your preferred doneness.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-feature-wrapper"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#129474; <strong>We use <a href="https://amzn.to/2OXdkZw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">Diamond Crystal kosher salt</a></strong> at about 1 teaspoon per pound of steak. If you're using Morton's or table salt, use less - they're saltier by volume!</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-2 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="ribeye steak seared in a cast iron skillet." class="wp-image-42169" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4.jpg" alt="ribeye steak seared in a cast iron skillet." class="wp-image-42169" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-4.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ol start="2" class="wp-block-list is-style-circle-number-list">
<li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Once your skillet is smoking hot, add <strong>oil</strong> and immediately add the steaks. Sear for 3-4 minutes per side (depending on thickness) until you get a gorgeous golden-brown crust. For medium-rare, we pull ours around 130&deg;F internal temp and let it rest. <br><br>Transfer the steaks to a plate and let them rest for at least 10 minutes before slicing. This keeps all those juices locked in!</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-branding-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#128161; <strong>Use a <a href="https://amzn.to/4r8CFfL" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">meat thermometer</a>!</strong> It's the only way to guarantee you don't overcook your steak. Pull it about 5&deg;F below your target temp since it'll keep cooking as it rests.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-3 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="seasoning shrimp with salt, pepper, red pepper flakes, and smoked paprika in a bowl." class="wp-image-42167" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2.jpg" alt="seasoning shrimp with salt, pepper, red pepper flakes, and smoked paprika in a bowl." class="wp-image-42167" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-2.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ol start="3" class="wp-block-list is-style-circle-number-list">
<li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Season your shrimp with salt, pepper, red pepper flakes, and smoked paprika. Give them a good toss to coat everything evenly.</li>
</ol>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="cooking shrimp in a hot cast iron skillet with butter." class="wp-image-42170" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5.jpg" alt="cooking shrimp in a hot cast iron skillet with butter." class="wp-image-42170" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-5.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>Add <strong>butter</strong> to the skillet to melt, then add the shrimp in a single layer. Don't crowd the pan - work in batches if needed! Sear for about 1-2 minutes per side until they're pink and just cooked through, then set aside with the steak.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-feature-wrapper"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#127844; <strong>Shrimp cook FAST!</strong> As soon as they turn opaque and curl slightly, they're done. Overcooked shrimp get rubbery, so keep a close eye on them.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-4 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="caramelized onion and garlic in a cast iron skillet with butter." class="wp-image-42171" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6.jpg" alt="caramelized onion and garlic in a cast iron skillet with butter." class="wp-image-42171" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-6.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ol start="4" class="wp-block-list is-style-circle-number-list">
<li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Add the remaining butter to the same skillet along with the diced <strong>onion</strong> and a pinch of salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the onion is softened and lightly browned - about 5-6 minutes. Add the <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for just 30 seconds until fragrant.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-branding-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#129476; <strong>Don't rush the onions!</strong> Letting them cook down until they're soft and golden adds so much depth and sweetness to the sauce.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-5 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="wilted spinach in a cast iron skillet with onions and garlic." class="wp-image-42172" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7.jpg" alt="wilted spinach in a cast iron skillet with onions and garlic." class="wp-image-42172" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-7.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ol start="5" class="wp-block-list is-style-circle-number-list">
<li><strong>Step 5:</strong> Toss in the chopped <strong>spinach</strong> with another pinch of salt. Stir it around the pan frequently - it'll wilt down fast!</li>
</ol>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="spinach with broth, garlic, onions, butter, lemon juice and zest, and seasonings." class="wp-image-42152" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8.jpg" alt="spinach with broth, garlic, onions, butter, lemon juice and zest, and seasonings." class="wp-image-42152" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-8.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>Once the spinach is wilted, add the <strong>lemon zest</strong> and <strong>broth</strong>. Let it simmer for 2-3 minutes to reduce slightly and concentrate those flavors.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-6 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="creamy sauce with spinach and fresh parmesan added with a rubber spatula in the skillet to stir." class="wp-image-42153" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9.jpg" alt="creamy sauce with spinach and fresh parmesan added with a rubber spatula in the skillet to stir." class="wp-image-42153" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-9.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ol start="6" class="wp-block-list is-style-circle-number-list">
<li><strong>Step 6:</strong> Stir in the <strong>heavy cream</strong>, then start adding the <strong>Parmesan cheese</strong> in small handfuls. Stir constantly and let each handful melt completely before adding more. This is the key to a silky-smooth sauce! </li>
</ol>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="creamy garlic parmesan cream sauce with spinach in a cast iron skillet." class="wp-image-42154" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10.jpg" alt="creamy garlic parmesan cream sauce with spinach in a cast iron skillet." class="wp-image-42154" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-10.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<p>Once all the parmesan is melted and the sauce is smooth and creamy, stir in the <strong>lemon juice</strong>. Taste and adjust the seasonings - you might want a little more salt, pepper, or lemon!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-feature-wrapper"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#129472; <strong>Fresh parmesan is a MUST!</strong> Pre-shredded cheese has anti-caking agents that prevent it from melting smoothly. Grate it yourself for the best results - your sauce will thank you.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-branding-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#127819; <strong>Add the lemon juice last!</strong> The acid can cause the cheese to seize up if you add it too early. Waiting until the end keeps everything silky.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>Add the steak and shrimp back to the skillet, nestling them into that gorgeous creamy sauce. Garnish with fresh<strong> parsley</strong> and a sprinkle of <strong>parmesan</strong>, then serve immediately!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1799" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201799'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="close up shot of well seasoned shrimp, and juicy medium rare steak bites on a parmesan cream sauce, topped with parsley and parmesan shavings." class="wp-image-42165" data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21-150x225.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1799" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21.jpg" alt="close up shot of well seasoned shrimp, and juicy medium rare steak bites on a parmesan cream sauce, topped with parsley and parmesan shavings." class="wp-image-42165" srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21.jpg 1200w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21-150x225.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Steak-and-Seafood-Recipe-21.jpg"></noscript></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-feature-wrapper"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p>&#10024; <strong>This is best served fresh</strong> while the sauce is hot and silky. If you have leftovers, store them in the fridge for up to 5 days and reheat gently - just know the steak will cook a bit more each time you reheat.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-perfect-sides-for-garlic-parmesan-steak-and-shrimp"><strong>Perfect Sides for Garlic Parmesan Steak and Shrimp</strong> &#129367;</h2>



<p>This is already a pretty complete meal with the protein and spinach built right in, but a great side dish never hurts! We love serving this with:</p>



<p><strong>Mashed potatoes</strong> - Our <a href="https://afullliving.com/buttermilk-mashed-potatoes/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer">creamy buttermilk mashed potatoes</a> or <a href="https://afullliving.com/truffle-mashed-potatoes/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer">indulgent truffle mash</a> are perfect for soaking up all that garlic parmesan sauce.</p>



<p><strong>Roasted vegetables</strong> - Some<em> </em><a href="https://afullliving.com/roasted-green-beans-carrots/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer">simple roasted carrots and green beans </a>add some color and freshness to the plate.</p>



<p><strong>Simple salad</strong> - Keep it light with a <a href="https://afullliving.com/arugula-spinach-salad/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer">fresh arugula spinach salad</a> on the side.</p>



<p><strong>Crusty bread</strong> - Honestly, you just need something to mop up every last drop of that creamy sauce!</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-group-asterisk"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p><strong>Want to go all out?</strong> If you want to make this meal extra special for date night, Valentine's Day, or the holidays, add some <a href="https://afullliving.com/butter-poached-lobster/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer">garlic butter lobster tails</a> or <a href="https://afullliving.com/baked-crab-legs/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer">baked crab legs </a>to really make it a showstopper surf and turf feast! &#129438;</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-feast-branding-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-leave-a-review"><strong>&#127775;Leave a Review!</strong></h2>



<p>If you make this <strong>Creamy Garlic Parmesan Surf and Turf</strong>, we'd love to hear from you! Leave a comment below and rate the recipe. Share with us by tagging us on <a href="https://www.instagram.com/afullliving/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener follow" data-wpel-link="exclude">Instagram</a>! We love seeing your creations!&#128248;</p>
</div></div>


<div id="recipe"></div><h2 class="feast-recipe-heading">📖 Recipe</h2><div id="wprm-recipe-container-26170" class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="26170" data-servings="6"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-chamere-chic-updated-recipe"><div class="wprm-container-float-right">
    <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-rounded"><img decoding="async" style="border-width: 0px;border-style: solid;border-color: #666666;border-radius: 3px;" width="250" height="250" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20250%20250'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-250x250 size-250x250" alt="Creamy parmesan steak and shrimp skillet with garlic cream sauce." data-lazy-srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-360x360.jpg 360w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-150x150.jpg 150w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-768x768.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-500x500.jpg 500w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-600x600.jpg 600w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-720x720.jpg 720w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-180x180.jpg 180w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-96x96.jpg 96w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-360x360.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" style="border-width: 0px;border-style: solid;border-color: #666666;border-radius: 3px;" width="250" height="250" src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-360x360.jpg" class="attachment-250x250 size-250x250" alt="Creamy parmesan steak and shrimp skillet with garlic cream sauce." srcset="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-360x360.jpg 360w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-150x150.jpg 150w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-768x768.jpg 768w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-500x500.jpg 500w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-600x600.jpg 600w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-720x720.jpg 720w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-180x180.jpg 180w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image-96x96.jpg 96w, https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px" data-pin-media="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Creamy-Parmesan-Steak-and-Shrimp-Skillet-Featured-Image.jpg"></noscript></div>
</div>
<h2 class="wprm-recipe-name wprm-block-text-bold">Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce</h2>
<div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
<span class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author wprm-block-text-light"><a href="https://afullliving.com/about" target="_self" data-wpel-link="internal" rel="noopener noreferrer">Briana</a></span>
<div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
<div class="wprm-recipe-summary wprm-block-text-normal"><span style="display: block;">This <strong>Steak and Shrimp Skillet with Garlic Parmesan Cream Sauce</strong> is one of our most popular recipes for good reason! Juicy ribeye steak and perfectly seared shrimp nestle into the most luscious, creamy garlic parmesan sauce with fresh spinach and a bright squeeze of lemon. It tastes like something you'd order at an upscale steakhouse, but it all comes together in one skillet in under an hour. Perfect for date night, Valentine's Day, anniversaries, or any time you want to feel fancy without the fuss. This surf and turf dinner has earned 75+ five-star reviews from readers who love how impressive it looks and how easy it actually is to make!</span></div>
<div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
